<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="533" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,930,1351]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1074,1099]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" box="[274,575,1074,1099]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Mastacembelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="perakensis">
<emphasis box="[274,575,1074,1099]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">Mastacembelus perakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Herre, A. W. C. T. &amp; Myers, G. S." box="[833,1085,1075,1099]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" pagination="5 - 75" refId="ref15145" refString="Herre, A. W. C. T. &amp; Myers, G. S. (1937) A contribution to the ichthyology of the Malay Peninsula. Bulletin of the Raffles Museum, 13, 5 - 75." type="journal article" year="1937">Herre &amp; Myers (1937)</bibRefCitation>
as they observed their material was different from its closest congener 
<taxonomicName box="[612,767,1110,1135]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Macrognathus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[612,767,1110,1135]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">M. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(without vs. with preopercular spine). Subsequently, Sufi (1956) reported that the presence of a preopercular spine may be variable in some Mastacembelids and the spine can be pungent or hidden beneath the skin. Thereon Sufi (1956) treated 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" box="[955,1112,1182,1207]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Mastacembelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="perakensis">
<emphasis box="[955,1112,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">M. perakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a doubtful species but he/ she did not examine the 
<typeStatus box="[425,527,1218,1243]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">holotype</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[588,686,1218,1243]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">holotype</typeStatus>
was eventually examined and confirmed to possess a preopercular spine by 
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, T. R." box="[264,438,1254,1279]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" pagination="1 - 210" refId="ref18023" refString="Roberts, T. R. (1989) The freshwater fishes of western Borneo (Kalimantan Barat, Indonesia). Memoirs of the California Academy of Sciences, 14, 1 - 210." type="journal article" year="1989">Roberts (1989)</bibRefCitation>
and it was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName box="[814,972,1254,1279]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Macrognathus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[814,972,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">M. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We note that 
<bibRefCitation author="Kottelat, M." box="[1157,1335,1254,1279]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" pagination="1 - 663" refId="ref15672" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of Southeast Asia: A catalogue and core bibliography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">Kottelat (2013)</bibRefCitation>
lists 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Mastacembelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="perakensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">M. perakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species although no reference is provided. We therefore follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, T. R." box="[1102,1271,1290,1315]" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" pagination="1 - 210" refId="ref18023" refString="Roberts, T. R. (1989) The freshwater fishes of western Borneo (Kalimantan Barat, Indonesia). Memoirs of the California Academy of Sciences, 14, 1 - 210." type="journal article" year="1989">Roberts (1989)</bibRefCitation>
by treating 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Herre &amp; Myers" authorityYear="1937" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Mastacembelus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="perakensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">M. perakensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[541,694,1326,1351]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Macrognathus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="18" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[541,694,1326,1351]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="533">M. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
